    <h1 class="set2-banr"><img src="/img/sections/advise.gif" alt="Advising &amp; tutoring services" width="480" height="32" /></h1>
<div id="pstrip" class="acad"></div>

    <div id="content">
      <div id="sidebar">
        <div id="infobox">
          <h3>Related</h3>
          <p><a href="https://notes.berkeley.edu/">ASUC Lecture Notes Online </a> (formerly Black Lightning)</p>
          <p>Textbooks: <a href="http://www.bkstr.com/CategoryDisplay/10001-10001-10433-1?demoKey=d">Cal Student Store</a></p>
        </div> <!-- end infobox -->
        <img src="/img/sidebar-pix/wheeler-200x150.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="150" /> </div> 
      <!-- end #sidebar -->
      <a name="maincontent" id="maincontent"></a>
          <p><a href="http://uga.berkeley.edu/uga/">Student Affairs</a>: Clearinghouse of information for undergraduate students.</p>
          <p><a href="http://slc.berkeley.edu/general/index.htm">Student Learning Center</a>:
            Support services to help students transition to Cal, navigate
            the academic terrain, create resource networks,
            and achieve their goals.</p>
          <p><a href="http://slas.berkeley.edu/">Student Life Advising
              Services</a>:
            Programs to enhance undergraduates' academic,
              personal, and social experience on campus. </p>
          <p><a href="http://ls-advise.berkeley.edu">Letters &amp; Science
              Office of Undergraduate Advising</a>: Assistance for L&amp;S
              students, to help them do academic planning, track progress
              toward degree, and understand academic policies and requirements.</p>
          <p><a href="http://ls.berkeley.edu/?q=undergraduate/preparing-graduate-school/step-step">Step by Step</a>: Guide to preparing for graduate school for Berkeley undergraduates in Arts & Humanities and Social Sciences.</p>
          <p><a href="http://academiccenters.reshall.berkeley.edu/">Residence
              Hall Academic Centers</a>: Academic support for residential
              students through academic advising, tutoring, faculty interaction,
              technology, and program services.</p>
          <p><a href="http://www.aad.berkeley.edu/">Academic
            Achievement Division</a>:
            Programs to help low-income
            and first-generation college students complete their undergraduate
            education  and go on to pursue advanced degrees. Component
            services include: </p>
          <ul class="indent">
            <li><a href="http://www.aad.berkeley.edu/sss.shtml">Student Support Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="http://www.aad.berkeley.edu/miller.shtml">Miller
              Scholars Program</a></li>
            <li><a href="http://www.aad.berkeley.edu/mcnair.shtml">McNair Scholars Program</a></li>
          </ul>
          <p> <a href="http://dsp.berkeley.edu">Disabled Students Program</a>:
            Services and accommodations for students with
            disabilities (including attention-deficit disorder and learning
            disabilities).</p>
          <p><a href="http://asc.berkeley.edu/">Athletic Study Center</a>:
            Academic support for student athletes.</p>
          <p><a href="http://myyears.berkeley.edu/">My Years at Cal</a>: Year by year blueprint for undergraduate student success, with advice, videos, and polls.</p>
          <p><a href="http://slc.berkeley.edu/studystrategies/">Study strategies</a>: Help, support and advice from the Student Learning Center.</p>

    </div>
